# Testing Rules

## Test structure
- Unit tests: mock ALL external calls (Ollama, ChromaDB, BM25)
- Integration tests: use fixtures from tests/fixtures/ — never real documents
- Every new pipeline step must have a corresponding test file

## Fixture rules
- Minimal valid Violation object must always be available as fixture
- Provide at least 2 fixture documents: well-structured DOCX + malformed DOCX
- ViolationContext fixture must cover: empty retrieval results + non-empty results

## What to always test
- Parser functions in prompts.py: valid JSON, missing fields, empty string, wrong type
- Pipeline steps with empty retrieval results (most common failure mode)
- Threshold boundary values from config.py (score exactly at threshold)

## Mock pattern (use this consistently)
```python
from unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock

@patch("rag_pipeline.OllamaClient")
def test_evaluator(mock_ollama):
    mock_ollama.return_value.generate.return_value = (
        '{"score": 0.75, "reasoning": "test"}'
    )
    # test code here
```

## What NOT to do
- Do not call real Ollama in unit tests — tests must run without Ollama running
- Do not use real ChromaDB collections in unit tests
- Do not test implementation details — test inputs and outputs of each step